1
00:00:02,970 --> 00:00:04,405
Bisky: My name’s
biscuit krueger,

2
00:00:04,438 --> 00:00:06,040
and i’m a professional hunter,

3
00:00:06,073 --> 00:00:08,142
but i’m not too big
on formalities,

4
00:00:08,175 --> 00:00:10,344
so you guys
can just call me bisky.

5
00:00:10,377 --> 00:00:12,479
In return, you must obey

6
00:00:12,513 --> 00:00:15,216
every word of what I teach you
without question.

7
00:00:15,249 --> 00:00:17,551
Killua: Ugh. No way,
and, no, thank you.

8
00:00:17,584 --> 00:00:19,252
He and I are not so desperate

9
00:00:19,286 --> 00:00:21,488
that we need to beg
a total stranger to train us,

10
00:00:21,522 --> 00:00:23,190
so you could
just forget about it.

11
00:00:23,223 --> 00:00:25,225
Am I right, gon? Back me up!

12
00:00:25,259 --> 00:00:27,394
Gon: Uh, thing is,
Mr. Wing is already training us.

13
00:00:27,427 --> 00:00:28,962
Killua: Yeah, that’s right!

14
00:00:28,996 --> 00:00:31,198
We already have a master.
Position’s filled,

15
00:00:31,231 --> 00:00:33,967
and we are not in the market
for another one.

16
00:00:34,001 --> 00:00:35,503
Bisky: Did you say wing?

17
00:00:35,536 --> 00:00:38,506
That little boy
with the messy hair and glasses?

18
00:00:38,539 --> 00:00:41,242
The one who never
tucks his shirt in?

19
00:00:41,275 --> 00:00:42,476
Gon: You know him?

20
00:00:42,509 --> 00:00:44,444
Bisky: Well,
of course I know him!

21
00:00:44,478 --> 00:00:47,081
Wing is one of my students,
or he was.

22
00:00:47,114 --> 00:00:48,182
Killua: Really?

23
00:00:48,215 --> 00:00:50,084
Gon: Wow!
What a coincidence, huh?

24
00:00:50,117 --> 00:00:53,053
Bisky: So wing’s
become a master now, has he?

25
00:00:53,086 --> 00:00:54,988
Time really does fly,
doesn’t it?

26
00:00:55,022 --> 00:00:58,359
Does that mean both of you are
professional hunters as well?

27
00:00:58,392 --> 00:01:00,027
Gon: Yeah. Well, just me.

28
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:02,629
Bisky: And you passed
the secret exam, too?

29
00:01:02,663 --> 00:01:03,998
Gon: Yep.

30
00:01:04,031 --> 00:01:06,700
Bisky: Wow,
that really takes me back.

31
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:10,303
I’d love to be
an examiner again.

32
00:01:10,337 --> 00:01:12,639
Well, I guess that would mean

33
00:01:12,673 --> 00:01:15,109
that I am essentially
your master’s master.

34
00:01:15,142 --> 00:01:18,746
Now that that’s out of the way,
let’s start training!

35
00:01:18,779 --> 00:01:19,747
♪

36
00:01:19,780 --> 00:01:21,649
( Singing in Japanese )

37
00:02:03,724 --> 00:02:05,726
♪

38
00:02:08,729 --> 00:02:10,831
Gon: That is so awesome!
You were really

39
00:02:10,864 --> 00:02:13,233
one of the examiners
for the hunter exam?

40
00:02:13,267 --> 00:02:16,203
Killua: Well, i’m not convinced
that she’s telling the truth.

41
00:02:16,236 --> 00:02:19,172
Bisky: You sure are a stubborn
little boy, aren’t you?

42
00:02:19,206 --> 00:02:21,208
That’s a good thing.
In kids, anyway.

43
00:02:21,241 --> 00:02:25,412
Now, you mentioned before that
you weren’t desperate, right?

44
00:02:25,445 --> 00:02:26,680
Book.

45
00:02:26,713 --> 00:02:28,315
Gon: What’s that card?

46
00:02:28,348 --> 00:02:31,117
Bisky: Notice that the
difficulty to obtain is rank d.

47
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:32,552
It’s a normal card

48
00:02:32,586 --> 00:02:35,322
that doesn’t go in
a specified slot in your book.

49
00:02:36,757 --> 00:02:38,392
There are a lot of people

50
00:02:38,425 --> 00:02:40,827
who could have obtained
this card without much trouble.

51
00:02:40,861 --> 00:02:43,230
The same
can’t be said for you two,

52
00:02:43,263 --> 00:02:44,731
and that’s the problem.

53
00:02:44,765 --> 00:02:48,202
If you run into someone
who’s stronger than you are

54
00:02:48,235 --> 00:02:50,537
or someone whose intentions
are completely evil--

55
00:02:51,772 --> 00:02:53,874
( gasps ) Quick, sit down.

56
00:02:53,907 --> 00:02:55,542
Pretend we’re just chatting.

57
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:58,745
There’s an enemy behind me.

58
00:02:58,779 --> 00:03:01,649
♪

59
00:03:01,682 --> 00:03:04,652
Man: Three kids’ll
be a walk in the park.

60
00:03:04,685 --> 00:03:06,253
( Giggles )

61
00:03:09,456 --> 00:03:11,425
I’ll tear them to shreds.

62
00:03:14,294 --> 00:03:16,229
Bisky: Don’t try to sense him.

63
00:03:16,263 --> 00:03:17,464
He’ll notice.

64
00:03:17,498 --> 00:03:19,533
Killua: Then how
did you sense him?

65
00:03:19,566 --> 00:03:21,601
Bisky: He let
his bloodlust leak out.

66
00:03:21,635 --> 00:03:24,538
It wasn’t much,
and it was just for a second,

67
00:03:24,571 --> 00:03:26,339
’cause he’s
not threatened by children.

68
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:28,742
Killua: He must be weak,
since he lost control.

69
00:03:28,775 --> 00:03:31,311
Bisky: But then he
concealed his presence again

70
00:03:31,345 --> 00:03:32,746
almost immediately.

71
00:03:32,779 --> 00:03:35,882
The bloodlust was minimal,
and his reaction was swift,

72
00:03:35,916 --> 00:03:38,352
so he’s very experienced.

73
00:03:38,385 --> 00:03:40,621
Killua: We couldn’t even
sense his presence,

74
00:03:40,654 --> 00:03:42,656
let alone locate him.

75
00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:46,160
What should we do now?

76
00:03:46,193 --> 00:03:48,395
Bisky: Wow,
he adjusts pretty quickly.

77
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:50,363
He’s a bright one.

78
00:03:50,397 --> 00:03:52,466
What do you think we should do?

79
00:03:52,499 --> 00:03:54,401
Gon: Well, we should
definitely stick together.

80
00:03:54,434 --> 00:03:55,635
Bisky: And why’s that?

81
00:03:55,669 --> 00:03:58,272
Gon: I think the reason
he tensed up again

82
00:03:58,305 --> 00:04:00,674
is because there are
three of us right here,

83
00:04:00,707 --> 00:04:02,309
so if we stick together,

84
00:04:02,342 --> 00:04:04,711
he might think twice
before attacking us.

85
00:04:04,745 --> 00:04:06,180
Killua: Yeah, I agree.

86
00:04:06,213 --> 00:04:08,782
Bisky: I guess
I can’t argue with that.

87
00:04:08,815 --> 00:04:11,885
But that’s
not what we’re going to do.

88
00:04:11,919 --> 00:04:14,388
You see, if I go off on my own,

89
00:04:14,421 --> 00:04:16,556
the enemy is almost guaranteed
to target me,

90
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:18,759
so i’ll go south,
and you head north.

91
00:04:18,792 --> 00:04:20,193
Walk about 500 meters

92
00:04:20,227 --> 00:04:22,496
without trying
to conceal your presence.

93
00:04:22,529 --> 00:04:24,664
Aim for that pillar.

94
00:04:24,698 --> 00:04:26,667
Once you get there, use zetsu.

95
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:28,402
Then get back here immediately.

96
00:04:28,435 --> 00:04:30,671
Killua: Right.
Stalking the stalker, huh?

97
00:04:34,575 --> 00:04:36,377
Gon: Huh?

98
00:04:36,410 --> 00:04:38,846
Bisky: Be that way,
you big dummy!

99
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:41,382
Killua: That damn hag.

100
00:04:41,415 --> 00:04:42,983
Bisky: I’ve had
just about enough!

101
00:04:43,016 --> 00:04:44,751
I’m leaving!

102
00:04:44,785 --> 00:04:47,755
Killua: Yeah, well, get lost,
and don’t come back, okay?!

103
00:04:47,788 --> 00:04:50,524
Come on. Let’s go.

104
00:04:50,557 --> 00:04:52,793
( Gon gasps ) It’s an act.

105
00:04:53,794 --> 00:04:55,996
Killua: So long, you idiot!

106
00:04:58,632 --> 00:05:00,000
( Man giggles )

107
00:05:00,033 --> 00:05:01,368
( Wind blowing )

108
00:05:01,401 --> 00:05:03,503
Killua: That woman
is pretty amazing.

109
00:05:03,537 --> 00:05:04,505
Gon: Huh?

110
00:05:04,538 --> 00:05:06,540
Killua: I was on high alert

111
00:05:06,573 --> 00:05:08,708
so i’d be ready for anything.

112
00:05:10,277 --> 00:05:12,713
Even so, I didn’t realize
what she’d done

113
00:05:12,746 --> 00:05:14,815
until my cheek
was already stinging.

114
00:05:22,556 --> 00:05:23,891
Now let’s hurry back.

115
00:05:23,924 --> 00:05:24,925
Gon: Yeah.

116
00:05:26,627 --> 00:05:27,928
( Scissors snipping )

117
00:05:27,961 --> 00:05:30,464
( Man laughing )

118
00:05:31,665 --> 00:05:33,734
♪

119
00:05:33,767 --> 00:05:37,437
I cut it! I just cut your hair.

120
00:05:37,471 --> 00:05:39,273
You see, that...

121
00:05:39,306 --> 00:05:43,710
Was my scissor hands:
Barber slasher!

122
00:05:45,078 --> 00:05:48,982
And now i’m gonna eat it.

123
00:05:49,983 --> 00:05:52,953
When I consume the hair I cut,

124
00:05:52,986 --> 00:05:55,489
I learn things about its owners

125
00:05:55,522 --> 00:05:57,824
that they don’t even
know about themselves.

126
00:05:57,858 --> 00:06:00,561
I absorb everything!

127
00:06:00,594 --> 00:06:03,630
Muscle tone,
potential for disease,

128
00:06:03,664 --> 00:06:05,866
genetic strengths,

129
00:06:05,899 --> 00:06:08,502
i’ll learn everything
there is about your body

130
00:06:08,535 --> 00:06:12,305
before I start
to toy with it, everything!

131
00:06:12,339 --> 00:06:13,340
( Gasps )

132
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:21,548
Wait! She’s 57 years old?!

133
00:06:21,582 --> 00:06:23,050
She doesn’t look it.

134
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:27,454
What’s even more surprising
is how honed her body is.

135
00:06:28,789 --> 00:06:30,057
I can tell.

136
00:06:30,090 --> 00:06:33,527
Her physical appearance
conceals the strength

137
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,862
that she’s achieved
through intensive training,

138
00:06:35,896 --> 00:06:38,465
decades of it, probably.

139
00:06:41,602 --> 00:06:44,572
If I may ask,
i’d like to spar with you.

140
00:06:44,605 --> 00:06:48,442
Bisky: So I guess you’re
not just trash after all.

141
00:06:48,475 --> 00:06:49,876
Fine. Let’s go.

142
00:07:08,595 --> 00:07:10,063
( Yells )

143
00:07:11,064 --> 00:07:12,532
( Man groans )

144
00:07:17,838 --> 00:07:19,740
♪

145
00:07:19,773 --> 00:07:21,408
Bisky: You’re really lucky.

146
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:25,045
In a nen battle,
I would have annihilated you.

147
00:07:25,078 --> 00:07:28,515
So during that fight,
what did you see first?

148
00:07:28,549 --> 00:07:29,984
Gon: The first thing I saw

149
00:07:30,017 --> 00:07:31,785
was that guy being flipped
through the air.

150
00:07:31,818 --> 00:07:33,019
Killua: Me, too.

151
00:07:33,053 --> 00:07:35,422
Gon: Her opponent
wasn’t weak at all.

152
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:37,824
Killua: She’s just
that powerful.

153
00:07:37,858 --> 00:07:40,160
Bisky: If he were
an in-game character,

154
00:07:40,194 --> 00:07:42,430
he’d be difficulty rank d,

155
00:07:42,462 --> 00:07:45,832
in other words, an instant
game-over for you boys.

156
00:07:45,866 --> 00:07:48,702
And I believe
that makes this the second time

157
00:07:48,735 --> 00:07:51,905
i’ve seen you escape death
by the skin of your teeth.

158
00:07:51,939 --> 00:07:54,508
How long do you think
your luck’ll hold out?

159
00:07:54,541 --> 00:07:55,942
Gon: So, hey, miss bisky--

160
00:07:55,976 --> 00:07:58,011
bisky:
Please just call me bisky.

161
00:07:58,045 --> 00:08:01,782
But if you insist on honorifics,
call me lady bisky!

162
00:08:01,815 --> 00:08:04,551
Killua: I think i’m
just gonna stick with "hag."

163
00:08:04,585 --> 00:08:06,954
( Screams )

164
00:08:06,987 --> 00:08:09,556
Gon: Okay, bisky,
why are you here?

165
00:08:09,590 --> 00:08:11,926
Bisky: I came here
to clear the game,

166
00:08:11,959 --> 00:08:13,961
but also there’s
a Jewel i’m looking for.

167
00:08:13,994 --> 00:08:15,662
Gon: A Jewel?

168
00:08:15,696 --> 00:08:18,732
Bisky: And it’s one that can
only be found around here.

169
00:08:18,765 --> 00:08:21,434
It’s specified slot number 81.

170
00:08:21,468 --> 00:08:23,036
It’s called blue planet.

171
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:24,572
What about you boys?

172
00:08:24,605 --> 00:08:26,073
Killua: I thought it was obvious

173
00:08:26,106 --> 00:08:28,008
that we’re here
to clear the game.

174
00:08:28,041 --> 00:08:30,644
Gon: Yeah, but also
my dad and his friends

175
00:08:30,677 --> 00:08:32,979
- actually made "greed island."
- Bisky: Really?

176
00:08:33,013 --> 00:08:36,149
Gon: I’m looking for him,
and I don’t know where to start,

177
00:08:36,183 --> 00:08:38,218
but this game
just might contain a clue

178
00:08:38,252 --> 00:08:39,887
about where I can find him.

179
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:41,655
Bisky: And who is your dad?

180
00:08:41,688 --> 00:08:42,989
Gon: His name’s ging freecss.

181
00:08:43,023 --> 00:08:44,892
- Bisky: Seriously?!
- Gon: You know him?

182
00:08:44,925 --> 00:08:46,794
Bisky: Yes,
of course I know him!

183
00:08:46,827 --> 00:08:49,596
Ging is famous!

184
00:08:49,630 --> 00:08:51,799
♪

185
00:08:51,832 --> 00:08:53,634
Chairman netero used to say

186
00:08:53,667 --> 00:08:57,604
he’s among the top five
nen users in the entire world.

187
00:09:01,909 --> 00:09:06,680
Gon: Bisky, if you’d be willing
to postpone your treasure hunt,

188
00:09:06,713 --> 00:09:09,216
we’d be honored
if you’d teach us nen.

189
00:09:09,249 --> 00:09:11,685
Bisky: So you
finally came around.

190
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:14,721
You should know in advance
that i’m no softie like wing.

191
00:09:14,755 --> 00:09:16,023
Are you ready?

192
00:09:16,056 --> 00:09:17,491
Gon: Yes, I am!

193
00:09:17,524 --> 00:09:18,492
Bisky: And you?

194
00:09:18,525 --> 00:09:20,027
Killua: I’ll be all right.

195
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:22,629
( Man coughing )

196
00:09:22,663 --> 00:09:25,199
Bisky: Now hurry
and take out your cards.

197
00:09:25,232 --> 00:09:26,233
Man: Book.

198
00:09:28,969 --> 00:09:30,938
Bisky: You get one chance.

199
00:09:30,971 --> 00:09:34,942
Evade these two successfully and
for two weeks, you understand?

200
00:09:34,975 --> 00:09:37,744
And if you do,
then i’ll let you go.

201
00:09:37,778 --> 00:09:39,146
However, if you’re
knocked unconscious

202
00:09:39,179 --> 00:09:41,248
or if you can’t
stand up anymore,

203
00:09:41,281 --> 00:09:43,750
i’ll just have to kill you.

204
00:09:43,784 --> 00:09:45,552
( Both grunt )

205
00:09:45,586 --> 00:09:48,756
Man: So I just have to avoid
their attacks, right?

206
00:09:48,789 --> 00:09:51,158
Doesn’t matter what I do to ’em?

207
00:09:51,191 --> 00:09:52,959
Bisky: That’s right.

208
00:09:52,993 --> 00:09:54,695
But there’s one rule.

209
00:09:54,728 --> 00:09:58,198
Under no circumstances are you
allowed to leave this crater.

210
00:09:58,232 --> 00:10:02,103
If you break this rule,
you lose, and I kill you.

211
00:10:02,135 --> 00:10:03,570
Killua: What about us?

212
00:10:03,604 --> 00:10:05,072
Bisky: The same rule applies.

213
00:10:05,105 --> 00:10:08,775
If you leave or if you
can’t beat him after two weeks,

214
00:10:08,809 --> 00:10:11,178
you will be punished.

215
00:10:11,211 --> 00:10:15,182
You are the bounty hunter
binolt, aren’t you?

216
00:10:15,215 --> 00:10:17,017
Binolt: Yeah.

217
00:10:17,050 --> 00:10:19,786
Bisky: He’s also
a bounty himself.

218
00:10:19,820 --> 00:10:21,221
He’s a brutal murderer.

219
00:10:22,789 --> 00:10:23,790
( Binolt chuckles )

220
00:10:25,158 --> 00:10:26,760
Bisky: Now begin!

221
00:10:30,797 --> 00:10:31,998
♪

222
00:10:31,999 --> 00:10:33,734
♪

223
00:10:40,541 --> 00:10:41,842
( Binolt exhales )

224
00:10:45,279 --> 00:10:46,914
Bisky: What are
you waiting for?!

225
00:10:46,947 --> 00:10:49,850
Are you going to stand there
while he heals his wounds?!

226
00:10:57,991 --> 00:10:59,759
Killua: If he
wasn’t hurt so bad,

227
00:10:59,793 --> 00:11:01,795
I would have lost my eye.

228
00:11:01,829 --> 00:11:03,798
( Binolt coughs )

229
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:10,070
Gon: I can’t find an opening.

230
00:11:11,338 --> 00:11:14,041
Killua: I wonder
if I should try using this,

231
00:11:14,074 --> 00:11:18,078
but it’s not like he’s gonna
stay still while I charge up.

232
00:11:18,111 --> 00:11:20,914
Let’s make this
a battle of attrition.

233
00:11:20,948 --> 00:11:22,183
Gon: What’s "attrition" mean?

234
00:11:22,216 --> 00:11:24,251
Killua: You go
and get a little rest.

235
00:11:24,284 --> 00:11:28,121
I’ll stay and keep an eye on him
for now and use these to attack.

236
00:11:28,155 --> 00:11:29,590
Switch every six hours.

237
00:11:29,623 --> 00:11:31,024
Gon: He’s using rocks?

238
00:11:31,058 --> 00:11:32,226
Good idea!

239
00:11:33,227 --> 00:11:34,795
( Binolt chuckles )

240
00:11:34,828 --> 00:11:35,962
Just what I need.

241
00:11:35,996 --> 00:11:38,165
If I can rest like this
for a week,

242
00:11:38,198 --> 00:11:39,800
i’ll be pretty much recovered,

243
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:43,003
and as soon as i’m healed,
I can finish them off.

244
00:11:53,213 --> 00:11:54,214
Bisky: Huh.

245
00:11:58,018 --> 00:12:00,020
♪

246
00:12:00,053 --> 00:12:02,188
( Binolt gasps ) A shield?!

247
00:12:05,025 --> 00:12:06,360
Bisky: That’s right!

248
00:12:06,393 --> 00:12:09,096
You’ll never defeat him
in an endurance test!

249
00:12:09,129 --> 00:12:10,864
Killua: That makes sense.

250
00:12:13,167 --> 00:12:14,769
Binolt: Damn.

251
00:12:15,802 --> 00:12:17,804
( Crashing )

252
00:12:25,913 --> 00:12:27,915
( Panting )

253
00:12:41,028 --> 00:12:42,363
So much endurance.

254
00:12:42,396 --> 00:12:44,798
I don’t have any time to rest!

255
00:12:44,832 --> 00:12:46,834
Bisky: Binolt is hurt,

256
00:12:46,867 --> 00:12:50,137
but overwhelming him in
half a day is still impressive.

257
00:12:50,170 --> 00:12:53,807
They know that in this fight,
their lives are on the line.

258
00:12:53,841 --> 00:12:56,210
Not bad.

259
00:12:56,243 --> 00:13:00,214
These two are gems in the rough!

260
00:13:00,247 --> 00:13:03,650
Look at that hard resolve
in his eyes,

261
00:13:03,684 --> 00:13:06,654
that bottomless,
unwavering potential!

262
00:13:06,687 --> 00:13:08,956
If properly cut
through training,

263
00:13:08,989 --> 00:13:14,228
he can be completely transformed
into a true diamond.

264
00:13:14,261 --> 00:13:17,197
And this one’s
a cool, calm blue.

265
00:13:17,231 --> 00:13:20,668
He looks unstable, but apply
the right amount of heat,

266
00:13:20,701 --> 00:13:23,003
and he can achieve
permanent strength,

267
00:13:23,036 --> 00:13:25,739
a true sapphire.

268
00:13:25,772 --> 00:13:28,408
( Sighs )
Why does my heart skip a beat

269
00:13:28,442 --> 00:13:31,679
whenever I see something
waiting to be polished?

270
00:13:31,712 --> 00:13:34,448
I’m gonna train them so hard!

271
00:13:38,485 --> 00:13:40,821
A forest of rocks.

272
00:13:40,854 --> 00:13:44,191
It impedes the enemy
while concealing their presence.

273
00:13:44,224 --> 00:13:46,426
This isn’t gonna take two weeks.

274
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:48,462
They’ll be done in a day.

275
00:14:03,343 --> 00:14:05,912
Looks like it’s game over
for you, old man.

276
00:14:05,946 --> 00:14:07,181
No! Killua, stop!

277
00:14:07,214 --> 00:14:10,117
( Binolt grunts )

278
00:14:10,150 --> 00:14:12,719
Killua: Why didn’t you
let me finish him off?

279
00:14:12,753 --> 00:14:14,388
Gon: We still have
plenty of time.

280
00:14:14,421 --> 00:14:17,057
Let’s keep going until we
can deal with him one-on-one.

281
00:14:17,090 --> 00:14:18,325
Killua: Huh?

282
00:14:18,358 --> 00:14:20,727
Gon: Stopping now
would be a waste of time.

283
00:14:20,761 --> 00:14:23,130
We’re both pretty much
in top form right now.

284
00:14:23,163 --> 00:14:25,932
( Binolt laughs )
You idiot.

285
00:14:25,966 --> 00:14:27,801
It’s my turn.

286
00:14:27,835 --> 00:14:29,337
I’ll cut you to pieces!

287
00:14:29,369 --> 00:14:31,338
Gon: Okay, but let’s
wait ’til tomorrow.

288
00:14:31,371 --> 00:14:33,139
Binolt: Huh?

289
00:14:33,173 --> 00:14:35,308
Gon: It’s just I can tell
you’re getting a lot slower,

290
00:14:35,342 --> 00:14:37,945
so you should probably go
and get a little rest.

291
00:14:37,978 --> 00:14:39,379
Killua: Hmm, he’s right.

292
00:14:39,413 --> 00:14:42,383
If it takes both of us
to beat somebody

293
00:14:42,416 --> 00:14:44,485
who’s badly injured
and completely exhausted,

294
00:14:44,518 --> 00:14:47,254
we’ll never be able
to beat anybody.

295
00:14:47,287 --> 00:14:50,357
( Animal howls )

296
00:14:56,096 --> 00:14:57,064
( Both grunt )

297
00:14:57,097 --> 00:14:58,966
( Binolt groans )

298
00:14:58,999 --> 00:15:01,468
Bisky: You won’t
be able to slip away,

299
00:15:01,502 --> 00:15:04,472
not now that their antennae
are so perfectly tuned.

300
00:15:04,505 --> 00:15:06,007
Sorry, binolt,

301
00:15:06,039 --> 00:15:09,809
but your potential pales
in comparison to theirs.

302
00:15:14,948 --> 00:15:17,384
- ( Crowd murmuring )
- ( Baby crying )

303
00:15:19,586 --> 00:15:21,288
Woman: My wallet’s missing.

304
00:15:21,321 --> 00:15:24,090
Man: Really? It was just there.

305
00:15:25,826 --> 00:15:27,294
Boy: ’scuse me.

306
00:15:27,327 --> 00:15:28,495
Both: Huh?

307
00:15:28,529 --> 00:15:32,099
Boy: You, uh, dropped this.

308
00:15:32,132 --> 00:15:33,300
( Gasps )

309
00:15:36,537 --> 00:15:38,339
( Gasping )

310
00:15:41,542 --> 00:15:44,512
Bisky: All right, day two.

311
00:15:44,545 --> 00:15:46,514
♪

312
00:15:46,547 --> 00:15:48,549
( Both grunting )

313
00:16:00,093 --> 00:16:02,262
Killua: He’s slowing down.

314
00:16:02,296 --> 00:16:04,865
No, we’re getting faster.

315
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,936
The difference is amazing.

316
00:16:09,970 --> 00:16:11,438
Training pays off that much more

317
00:16:11,471 --> 00:16:13,139
when you’re fighting
for your life

318
00:16:13,173 --> 00:16:15,342
against one of your equals.

319
00:16:19,580 --> 00:16:21,348
( Yells )

320
00:16:21,381 --> 00:16:23,149
Bisky: Damn it.

321
00:16:23,183 --> 00:16:25,552
♪

322
00:16:25,586 --> 00:16:27,955
Damn it!

323
00:16:27,988 --> 00:16:30,924
( Gon yells )

324
00:16:30,958 --> 00:16:32,359
Binolt: No.

325
00:16:32,392 --> 00:16:35,161
This isn’t the life I wanted.

326
00:16:35,195 --> 00:16:37,964
I never asked for this!

327
00:16:37,998 --> 00:16:39,933
( Objects clatter )

328
00:16:41,301 --> 00:16:43,370
Woman: I warned you, didn’t I?

329
00:16:43,403 --> 00:16:44,604
Man: You were the one

330
00:16:44,638 --> 00:16:46,473
who suggested
that we take a shortcut!

331
00:16:46,507 --> 00:16:48,275
Woman: So it’s my fault?

332
00:16:48,308 --> 00:16:51,878
Man: Just look at my clothes!
They’re covered in filth!

333
00:16:51,912 --> 00:16:55,482
Binolt: It’s not like I was
asking for a reward or anything.

334
00:16:55,516 --> 00:16:58,886
I didn’t even expect
a thank-you.

335
00:16:58,919 --> 00:17:00,687
I just...

336
00:17:03,023 --> 00:17:04,324
( Killua grunts )

337
00:17:04,358 --> 00:17:06,594
Binolt: Enough already.

338
00:17:08,162 --> 00:17:10,197
There’s no way I can beat you.

339
00:17:10,230 --> 00:17:11,398
Just kill me.

340
00:17:11,431 --> 00:17:14,401
Gon: But why would we
want to do that?

341
00:17:14,434 --> 00:17:16,069
We’ve gotten a whole lot better,

342
00:17:16,103 --> 00:17:17,605
and it’s all
thanks to your help,

343
00:17:17,638 --> 00:17:20,241
so thank you, Mr. Binolt.

344
00:17:21,408 --> 00:17:23,176
Binolt: All I wanted...

345
00:17:24,311 --> 00:17:27,314
Was to live
as a decent human being.

346
00:17:31,652 --> 00:17:33,053
Bisky: You may go.

347
00:17:35,322 --> 00:17:38,225
Binolt: I’ll go turn myself in.

348
00:17:41,461 --> 00:17:42,629
Bisky: Gon...

349
00:17:42,663 --> 00:17:45,332
You certainly are
a flawless specimen,

350
00:17:45,365 --> 00:17:47,067
but that purity of yours

351
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:50,103
is going to make this
quite the balancing act.

352
00:17:52,272 --> 00:17:55,575
Okay! It’s time
we head to masadora!

353
00:17:55,609 --> 00:17:56,944
Both: Osu!

354
00:17:56,977 --> 00:17:59,146
( Both gasp )
The number nine!

355
00:17:59,179 --> 00:18:02,149
Bisky: Too slow!
Now give me 3,000 push-ups!

356
00:18:02,182 --> 00:18:04,351
Both: Damn it!

357
00:18:04,384 --> 00:18:06,119
Bisky: 70 kilometers to go

358
00:18:06,153 --> 00:18:09,156
in, oh, say, three hours?
Should be a breeze.

359
00:18:09,189 --> 00:18:11,558
Both: Seriously?!

360
00:18:11,592 --> 00:18:13,594
♪

361
00:18:21,401 --> 00:18:23,069
Gon: Hey, we’re here!

362
00:18:23,103 --> 00:18:24,404
Bisky: Come on!

363
00:18:24,438 --> 00:18:26,440
Help me
look for a department store!

364
00:18:27,474 --> 00:18:29,009
Gon: Just like we thought,

365
00:18:29,042 --> 00:18:30,410
they’re only selling cards here.

366
00:18:30,444 --> 00:18:32,146
Bisky: Sorry for the wait.

367
00:18:32,179 --> 00:18:34,682
Now let’s head
back to that rocky area.

368
00:18:34,715 --> 00:18:36,584
Both: What?!

369
00:18:36,617 --> 00:18:38,619
( Panting )

370
00:18:39,620 --> 00:18:40,788
Bisky: Gain!

371
00:18:42,422 --> 00:18:43,690
Gon: Wait. These are the cards

372
00:18:43,724 --> 00:18:45,259
you bought
at the department store?

373
00:18:45,292 --> 00:18:46,493
Bisky: Sure are.

374
00:18:46,527 --> 00:18:49,530
Okay, let’s head back
to masadora now,

375
00:18:49,563 --> 00:18:52,399
but this time,
we go in a straight line!

376
00:18:52,432 --> 00:18:54,334
Killua: Wait.
A straight line, huh?

377
00:18:54,368 --> 00:18:55,603
You don’t mean--

378
00:18:55,636 --> 00:18:57,238
bisky: I do!

379
00:18:57,271 --> 00:19:01,108
It’s time to start digging!

380
00:19:03,744 --> 00:19:05,779
Killua: Not as hard
as I was expecting.

381
00:19:05,812 --> 00:19:08,715
Gon: Yeah, it should go pretty
smoothly if this keeps up.

382
00:19:08,749 --> 00:19:11,385
♪

383
00:19:21,061 --> 00:19:22,195
( Both groan )

384
00:19:22,229 --> 00:19:23,197
Killua: This is rough.

385
00:19:23,230 --> 00:19:25,799
Gon: I can’t do any more.

386
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:28,636
Bisky: What are you doing?
Sit up if you’re gonna rest.

387
00:19:28,669 --> 00:19:30,104
- ( Killua groans )
- Gon: Huh?

388
00:19:30,137 --> 00:19:32,373
Bisky: Starting today,
this is how you sleep.

389
00:19:32,406 --> 00:19:34,174
Don’t let go of the rope.

390
00:19:34,208 --> 00:19:36,277
There’s always
a chance I might cut it,

391
00:19:36,310 --> 00:19:38,679
so keep part of your brain
on high alert,

392
00:19:38,712 --> 00:19:39,813
even when you’re sleeping.

393
00:19:41,348 --> 00:19:43,183
Killua: My dad
used to put me through

394
00:19:43,217 --> 00:19:44,752
this kind of training
all the time.

395
00:19:52,292 --> 00:19:54,594
Gon: Ow! That really hurt!

396
00:19:54,628 --> 00:19:56,063
Bisky: One more thing,

397
00:19:56,096 --> 00:19:59,266
when it falls,
you have to put it back up.

398
00:19:59,299 --> 00:20:02,068
( Digging )

399
00:20:02,102 --> 00:20:04,371
Killua: Oh, man, your head.

400
00:20:04,404 --> 00:20:05,772
Gon: I feel fine.

401
00:20:05,806 --> 00:20:08,676
Bisky: I’ll be
making the rocks bigger.

402
00:20:08,709 --> 00:20:09,843
Killua: Hey, gon--

403
00:20:09,877 --> 00:20:11,879
gon: I said i’m fine.

404
00:20:14,748 --> 00:20:17,517
( Yells )

405
00:20:19,319 --> 00:20:21,855
This rock is a lot harder
than the rest of it.

406
00:20:21,889 --> 00:20:23,657
Killua: Maybe we can dig it up.

407
00:20:23,690 --> 00:20:26,126
Gon: Hmm. I don’t think
the shovel’s gonna work.

408
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,628
But I think it might be possible

409
00:20:27,661 --> 00:20:30,297
for me to bust it open
with a nen punch. ( Gasps )

410
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:31,598
Killua: What’s wrong?

411
00:20:31,632 --> 00:20:33,601
Gon: Killua, what are you
doing with your aura

412
00:20:33,634 --> 00:20:35,302
when you’re digging?

413
00:20:35,335 --> 00:20:37,504
Killua: Nothing that’s
out of the ordinary, I guess.

414
00:20:37,538 --> 00:20:40,408
Try thinking of the shovel
as an extension of your body.

415
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:41,408
( Killua gasps )

416
00:20:41,441 --> 00:20:43,143
I see.

417
00:20:43,177 --> 00:20:45,613
If we envelop
the shovel in aura,

418
00:20:45,646 --> 00:20:47,581
our digging will be enhanced.

419
00:20:49,249 --> 00:20:52,252
Gon: Wow! It’s like
the rock’s made of custard!

420
00:20:52,286 --> 00:20:54,421
Killua: Okay!
Then let’s keep digging!

421
00:20:54,454 --> 00:20:56,122
Bisky: It sounds
like they’ve learned

422
00:20:56,156 --> 00:21:00,127
a new application of ten, shu!

423
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:04,431
They’ll complete the first phase
by the time we reach masadora.

424
00:21:05,499 --> 00:21:07,201
♪

425
00:21:07,234 --> 00:21:10,671
Narrator: Bisky’s grueling
training process is under way,

426
00:21:10,704 --> 00:21:14,608
but how it will affect the boys
remains to be seen.

427
00:21:15,609 --> 00:21:17,611
( Singing in Japanese )

